      <div class="stage-side"><div class="stage-number">05</div></div>
      <div class="stage-main">
        <div class="stage-eyebrow">Long-term optimisation — the surveillance that keeps him in surveillance</div>
        <h2 class="stage-title">Mark stays in the cohort. The quarterly PSA happens at home. The annual imaging happens in clinic. The trend stays stable. The cohort grows. Adam holds more patients in surveillance than the clinic-only model could have, and Mark is one of them. <span class="hm-witness" data-moment="mark-s5"></span></h2>

        <div class="stage-image" style="padding:0;border:none;background:none;margin-bottom:22px;"><img src="Assets/Mark Story/mark-stage5.png" alt="Mark Stage 5" style="width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:12px;display:block;box-shadow:0 8px 24px rgba(0,32,64,0.12);"></div>

        <div class="pull-quote">
          <p class="pull-quote-text">It is just part of life now. The kit comes when it is supposed to, I do it, I get on with my week. The hospital is for when something actually needs me there.</p>
          <div class="pull-quote-attribution">Mark</div>
        </div>

        <div class="whats-happening">
          <div class="whats-happening-label">What is happening</div>
          <div class="whats-happening-body">Active surveillance retention is the metric that matters: holding patients in the protocol so disease progression is caught early. Home PSA flattens the drop-out curve and keeps the cohort visible to the clinical team.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="old-way">
          <div class="old-way-label">The old way</div>
          <div class="old-way-body">Drop out of surveillance, progress unmonitored, present later with a different staging and a different prognosis. The clinical risk was always in the venue, not the patient.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="careteam">
          <div class="careteam-icon">&#x1F465;</div>
          <div class="careteam-body">
            <div class="careteam-label">Who is in the loop</div>
            <div class="careteam-text">Adam. The MDT. Mark.</div>
          </div>
